#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:4
msgid "Crowdfund"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:10
msgid ""
"This is example code for learning purposes. Do not use in production without "
"thorough review and testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:12
msgid ""
"Now, let's explore a straightforward example for a crowdfunding contract "
"where prospective participants can contribute funds to a campaign. If the "
"total contribution to the campaign reaches or surpasses a predetermined "
"funding goal, the funds will be sent to the  beneficiary at the end of the "
"campaign deadline. Participants will be refunded their respective "
"contributions if the total funding does not reach its target goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:19
msgid ""
"#pragma version >0.3.10\n"
"\n"
"###########################################################################\n"
"## THIS IS EXAMPLE CODE, NOT MEANT TO BE USED IN PRODUCTION! CAVEAT EMPTOR!\n"
"###########################################################################\n"
"\n"
"# example of a crowd funding contract\n"
"\n"
"funders: HashMap[address, uint256]\n"
"beneficiary: address\n"
"deadline: public(uint256)\n"
"goal: public(uint256)\n"
"timelimit: public(uint256)\n"
"finalized: bool\n"
"\n"
"# Setup global variables\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(_beneficiary: address, _goal: uint256, _timelimit: uint256):\n"
"    self.beneficiary = _beneficiary\n"
"    self.deadline = block.timestamp + _timelimit\n"
"    self.timelimit = _timelimit\n"
"    assert _goal > 0, \"Goal must be non-zero\"\n"
"    self.goal = _goal\n"
"\n"
"# Participate in this crowdfunding campaign\n"
"@external\n"
"@payable\n"
"def participate():\n"
"    assert block.timestamp < self.deadline, \"deadline has expired\"\n"
"    assert not self.finalized\n"
"\n"
"    self.funders[msg.sender] += msg.value\n"
"\n"
"# Enough money was raised! Send funds to the beneficiary\n"
"@external\n"
"def finalize():\n"
"    assert block.timestamp >= self.deadline, \"deadline has not expired "
"yet\"\n"
"    assert self.balance >= self.goal, \"goal has not been reached\"\n"
"    assert self.balance > 0\n"
"    self.finalized = True\n"
"\n"
"    send(self.beneficiary, self.balance)\n"
"\n"
"# Let participants withdraw their fund\n"
"@external\n"
"def refund():\n"
"    assert block.timestamp >= self.deadline and self.balance < self.goal\n"
"    assert not self.finalized\n"
"    assert self.funders[msg.sender] > 0\n"
"\n"
"    value: uint256 = self.funders[msg.sender]\n"
"    self.funders[msg.sender] = 0\n"
"\n"
"    send(msg.sender, value)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:23
msgid ""
"Most of this code should be relatively straightforward after going through "
"our previous examples. Let's dive right in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:26
msgid ""
"funders: HashMap[address, uint256]\n"
"beneficiary: address\n"
"deadline: public(uint256)\n"
"goal: public(uint256)\n"
"timelimit: public(uint256)\n"
"finalized: bool\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:31
msgid ""
"Like other examples, we begin by initiating our variables. Some variables "
"like ``deadline``, ``goal`` and ``timelimit`` are declared with the "
"``public`` function, making them readable by external callers. Variables "
"without ``public`` are, by default, private."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:37
msgid ""
"Unlike the existence of the function ``public()``, there is no equivalent "
"``private()`` function. Variables simply default to private if initiated "
"without the ``public()`` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:41
msgid ""
"The ``funders`` variable is initiated as a mapping where the key is an "
"address, and the value is a number representing the contribution of each "
"participant. The ``beneficiary`` will be the final receiver of the funds "
"once the crowdfunding period is over—as determined by the ``deadline`` and "
"``timelimit`` variables. The ``goal`` variable is the target total "
"contribution of all participants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:48
msgid ""
"# Setup global variables\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(_beneficiary: address, _goal: uint256, _timelimit: uint256):\n"
"    self.beneficiary = _beneficiary\n"
"    self.deadline = block.timestamp + _timelimit\n"
"    self.timelimit = _timelimit\n"
"    assert _goal > 0, \"Goal must be non-zero\"\n"
"    self.goal = _goal\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:53
msgid ""
"Our constructor function takes 3 arguments: the beneficiary's address, the "
"goal in wei value, and the difference in time from start to finish of the "
"crowdfunding. We initialize the arguments as contract variables with their "
"corresponding names. Additionally, a ``self.deadline`` is initialized to set "
"a definitive end time for the crowdfunding period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:59
msgid "Now let's take a look at how a person can participate in the crowdfund."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:61
msgid ""
"# Participate in this crowdfunding campaign\n"
"@external\n"
"@payable\n"
"def participate():\n"
"    assert block.timestamp < self.deadline, \"deadline has expired\"\n"
"    assert not self.finalized\n"
"\n"
"    self.funders[msg.sender] += msg.value\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:66
msgid ""
"Once again, we see the ``@payable`` decorator on a method, which allows a "
"person to send some ether along with a call to the method. In this case, the "
"``participate()`` method accesses the sender's address with ``msg.sender`` "
"and the corresponding amount sent with ``msg.value``. The contribution is "
"added to the ``funders`` HashMap, which maps each participant's address to "
"their total contribution amount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:73
msgid ""
"# Enough money was raised! Send funds to the beneficiary\n"
"@external\n"
"def finalize():\n"
"    assert block.timestamp >= self.deadline, \"deadline has not expired "
"yet\"\n"
"    assert self.balance >= self.goal, \"goal has not been reached\"\n"
"    assert self.balance > 0\n"
"    self.finalized = True\n"
"\n"
"    send(self.beneficiary, self.balance)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:78
msgid ""
"The ``finalize()`` method is used to complete the crowdfunding process. "
"However, to complete the crowdfunding, the method first checks to see if the "
"crowdfunding period is over and that the balance has reached/passed its set "
"goal. If those two conditions pass, the contract sends the collected funds "
"to the beneficiary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:84
msgid ""
"Notice that we have access to the total amount sent to the contract by "
"calling ``self.balance``, a variable we never explicitly set. Similar to "
"``msg`` and ``block``, ``self.balance`` is a built-in variable that's "
"available in all Vyper contracts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:89
msgid ""
"We can finalize the campaign if all goes well, but what happens if the "
"crowdfunding campaign isn't successful? We're going to need a way to refund "
"all the participants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:93
msgid ""
"# Let participants withdraw their fund\n"
"@external\n"
"def refund():\n"
"    assert block.timestamp >= self.deadline and self.balance < self.goal\n"
"    assert not self.finalized\n"
"    assert self.funders[msg.sender] > 0\n"
"\n"
"    value: uint256 = self.funders[msg.sender]\n"
"    self.funders[msg.sender] = 0\n"
"\n"
"    send(msg.sender, value)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/crowdfund.rst:98
msgid ""
"In the ``refund()`` method, we first check that the crowdfunding period is "
"indeed over and that the total collected balance is less than the ``goal`` "
"with the  ``assert`` statement . If those two conditions pass, we let users "
"get their funds back using the withdraw pattern."
msgstr ""

